-- Nardelli Named to Head Cerberus-Controlled Gunmaker
-- B y   C h a r l e s   S t e i n
-- 2010-09-24T14:21:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-24/nardelli-is-named-temporary-head-of-cerberus-controlled-gunmaker-freedom.html
Robert Nardelli , former chief
executive officer of Chrysler LLC and  Home Depot Inc ., was named
the temporary head of Freedom Group Inc. while the gunmaker
looks for a permanent CEO, according to a statement today.  Nardelli runs a unit of Cerberus Capital Management LP, a
New York-based buyout firm that controls Freedom, whose best-
known brand is Remington firearms.  Theodore Torbeck  resigned
earlier this month as CEO of the Madison, North Carolina-based
company, which filed for an initial public offering last year.  Nardelli, 62, was ousted as head of Atlanta-based Home
Depot in 2007 amid criticism of his pay and the companyâ€™s
lagging performance. He ran Chrysler for Cerberus until 2009
when the carmaker filed for bankruptcy after one of the worst
sales slumps in decades.  Private-equity firms pool investor money to take over
companies, financing the purchases mostly with debt, with the
intention of selling them later for a profit.  To contact the reporter on this story:
